OL,6,FKathy Stoker, whose father Norman is
OL,7,Flooked after at the home said, "He
OL,8,Fknows all the residents, they all sit
OL,9,Faround a large table for dinner, the
OL,10,Fcommunity spirit there is fantastic
OL,11,Fand the nurses and care workers there
OL,12,Ftreat him like family."
OL,14,FJulie Swift whose 95-year-old mother
OL,15,FHazel lives at the care home, said,
OL,16,F"She keeps ringing in tears, she
OL,17,Fdoesn't know what's going to happen in
OL,18,Fthe future and where she's going to be
OL,19,For if it could it be further away,
OL,20,Fit's awful."
